CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper November 5, 1955, pg. 8B, reads: "Honored - Incumbent District Attorney James F. Malone Jr. (R) was one of two candidates, up for re-election Tuesday, who was cited for having 'discharged the public trust with honesty, efficiency and without prejudice' by the State Association of Elks, at the Greater Pittsburgh Lodge, 115, Sunday night. Commissioner of Golf, Peter Dillard, is shown on the right. District Deputy Oscar Prince is on the left. Dr. Adolphus W. Anderson Sr., association president, made the citation. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Dr. Adolphus W. Anderson Sr. presenting Elks citation to District Attorney James F. Malone Jr., surrounded by men including Oscar Price on left and Peter Dillard on right, in Greater Pittsburgh Elks Lodge 115
